column5: All right...I'll bite...  Just you with a little too much time on your hands again?? Or are you guys working on one?  If you are, put me down for a subscription....LOL  Cliff
Do we get the subscriptions the same place we find the jumla`s?
LOL...it's that thick?  What did you do?  Print out every thread for the past year?
Rick, if every issue is going to be that thick it'll be one heck of a print job!  So where do I subscribe?  BTW, how did the lock issue work out?  Stan
Is this serious?  I will buy several copies if it is.  One for the living room, one for the bathroom, one for the garage, one for the bedroom, one for the dinnertable  my 2 cents  2many
You guys gotta get this magazine! Very innovative. Cost effective as well. The centerfold is a dwarf that doesn't need folding...it only took a quarter page.
LOL Roy and Rick "Postage paid in Sturgeon Falls"! They have printers up in them thar sticks?
No thanks, I already subscribed at the office.
where do i get my copy? Need some reading for this cold weather.
Hahahahaha Roy, thanks for the laugh dear.  That book's almost thick enough for Roy to use as a booster seat  Joey
Attn Admins  Is this a real mag or a joke.  I think it would be a great idea.  I need some answers  my 2 cents  2many
Don't forget the one for the John!  FHR
If were are to try and stay un-political then why is Jack leyton on the cover of the first issue?  Sorry I just couldn't resist!
That can't be Jack Layton. The boat in the picture is still floating.
